        <details>
            <summary>Dim sum culture</summary>
            Guangdong Province is also known for its tradition of "yum cha," which translates to "drinking tea" in Cantonese. Yum cha involves enjoying small bites of food, called "dim sum," which are paired with Chinese tea. Dim sum refers to a wide variety of dishes, excluding main courses and soups, ranging from savory to sweet. There are now over 800 types of dim sum, with each region of China having its own unique variations. However, dim sum from the Guangdong region is particularly famous.
        </details>
